The paper deals with the Delaunay triangulation, which is a fundamental topic in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the problem of approximating a point-cloud data set with a simplical complex, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves geometric reasoning and analysis, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.GT (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper discusses the Delaunay triangulation in different geometries, which could potentially fall under cs.MG (Mathematical Physics).
